==English==

===Noun===
'''gap'''  (''plural:'' '''[[gaps]]''')
# An opening in anything made by breaking or parting; as, a gap in a fence
#: ''He made a '''gap''' by kicking a weak spot.'' 
# An opening for a passage or entrance
#: ''We can slip through that '''gap'''.''
# An opening which implies a breach or defect
#: ''There is a '''gap''' between the roof and the gutter.''
# A vacant space or time
#: ''I have a '''gap''' in my schedule next Tuesday.''
# A hiatus.
#: ''I'm taking a '''gap'''.''
# A mountain pass.
#: ''The exploring party went through the high '''gap''' in the mountains.''
# {{baseball}} The regions between the [[outfielder]]s.
#: ''Jones doubled through the '''gap'''.''

